{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 BinbinHfr Reaper's Scripts Repository\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To install these scripts, you need to have ReaPack installed first. Get it for your platform/OS here :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://reapack.com/\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Then, import my repository into your Reapack, copying this link :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DaveInDev/Binbinhfr-Scripts/master/index.xml\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This page explains how to do it :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://reapack.com/user-guide#import-repositories\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Then search for "binbinhfr" in the package list, and install the scripts you need. They will appear in your action's list in Reaper.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Scripts :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Lyricator (import and display smoothly scrolling lyrics in a separate window)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Clean selected items of useless sustain pedal CC64\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Transpose selected midi or audio items by semitones\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Trim selected items (deleting any invisible part)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Adaptative Horizontal Zoom with Mousewheel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Legato notes of selected items to avoid overlapping notes (but keeping chords)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Effects :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab MIDI Keyboard Sensitivity (keyboard touch)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab MIDI Velocity Compressor with AutoGain\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Simple Smooth Gain (smootly adds or removes gain to the audio signal)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab MIDI Transpose Project/Track (global MIDI transpose of a project)\sa180\par}
}
